<![CDATA[<P>Dear {!Contact.FirstName},</P>
<P><?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">In mid-September, schools throughout the country will celebrate <SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold">Constitution Day, </SPAN>commemorating the signing of the U.S. Constitution.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</SPAN>American Student Assistance<SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Â®</SPAN> (ASA) is your resource for this important celebration!</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">In 2004, legislation that created Constitution Day required <SPAN style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold">all educational institutions who are receiving federal aid </SPAN>to implement educational programs about the U.S. Constitution on September 17<SUP>th</SUP> of each year, the anniversary of the actual signing of the Constitution in 1787.</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Since September 17 falls on a Monday, celebrations can occur the week before or the week after, providing schools greater flexibility.</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">ASA has a page dedicated to <A href="http://www.amsa.com/fap/resources/constitutionday.cfm"><SPAN style="COLOR: windowtext">Constitution Day</SPAN></A> complete with an implementation guide and resources to help you plan your celebration.</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">While you are on www.amsa.com, be sure to check out the <A href="http://www.amsa.com/fap/policies/manual.cfm"><SPAN style="COLOR: windowtext">Common Manual e-Collection</SPAN></A>, read highlights from the <A href="http://www.amsa.com/events/symposium/2007/index.cfm"><SPAN style="COLOR: windowtext">2007 Symposium</SPAN></A>, or stock up on <A href="http://www.amsa.com/fap/forms/index.cfm"><SPAN style="COLOR: windowtext">federal forms and ASA publications</SPAN></A>.</P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></P>
<P style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; LINE-HEIGHT: normal"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">If you have questions about Constitution Day or about any of ASA's services, please let me know!&nbsp; </SPAN>
<P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">
